 Police in Rongo Sub-County are tracing a woman who dumped her two-month-old baby at the doorstep of Rongo G4S offices.
Rongo Sub-County Police Commander, Mr Peter Okiring, said the infant was spotted by local traders on Tuesday night.
“Women who were from the market heard the baby crying in the cold and alerted authorities who went for her. We are tracing the whereabouts of the mother,” Mr Okiring said.



